{
  "stem": "22174.6",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "They stopped writing letters, because-- and they started writing postcards because they figured that, on postcards, they could write more openly because a censor wouldn't think-- wouldn't think to-- to that people would write anything objectionable, you know, dangerous, on a postcard.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So these postcards are really more explicit and-- about the situation than the letters were.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I still have those postcards.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I-- and I gave it to the Holocaust Center and translated it.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But-- and it's really-- it was very painful to translate.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I didn't expect it to be, but it was.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And from those postcards, I learned also a lot.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And the when the war broke out, September 1939, and then in October 19, I joined the British Army.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And met-- so I had-- had no more address in Haifa.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So my-- so my mother didn't know where to-- where to address these postcards.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So she addressed them to my uncle Tel Aviv.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And he, in turn, then gave-- somehow-- somehow got them to me, you know?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "When I was on leave, whenever there was a leave or something.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "This last one I got, I got through the military mail.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And so-- [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And my mother, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] I learned about my mother living in my hometown in Stendel until she was deported that she was with friends, friends or customers, not Jews-- non-- non-Jews took care of her.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You know, Jews weren't not even allowed anymore to go into food stores and buy food.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So friends of my family yes, and old customers brought her-- brought her food.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Then my cousins, after the-- [INAUDIBLE] letters to my-- to my-- to my sister with my-- these two cousins in Berlin.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
